cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.CY

This paper discusses the security implications of anti-virus software and how malware signatures can be used to launch attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the need to improve pattern-based signatures, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and system infrastructure (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of virus scanners, which falls under the category of systems and information (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for cyber attacks, which falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CY).
